	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey,
<br />
<br />When making an eprom cart using a SLROM board the eprom conversion sheet doesn't mention 27c1000 chips. I assume all would be the same aside from pin 24 not being needed to be bent up nor pin 2 needing to go under 24 on the pcb for either chr or pgm do to the pinout of the 27c1000 being closer to that of what nintendo used on their production roms correct? AKA anyone got a shematic to use 27c1000's for the SLROM board type please?
<br />
<br />Shawn

		

